== a builtin name:
shit: 1:1: warning: The which command is non-standard, use command -v for a portable lookup.
     1 |  which echo
       |  ^~~~~ here.
echo
== an absent name exits 1 with no output:
shit: 1:1: warning: The which command is non-standard, use command -v for a portable lookup.
     1 |  which definitely_absent_xyz
       |  ^~~~~ here.
rc=1
== a program resolved in a temp PATH:
shit: 1:1: warning: The which command is non-standard, use command -v for a portable lookup.
     1 |  which mytool
       |  ^~~~~ here.
TMPDIR/mytool
== -a lists every match in the temp PATH:
shit: 1:1: warning: The which command is non-standard, use command -v for a portable lookup.
     1 |  which -a mytool
       |  ^~~~~ here.
TMPDIR/mytool
